The paper discusses a technique for robot localization using a combination of acting and planning, which falls under the field of robotics (cs.RO). The approach involves using perception to reduce uncertainty, which involves techniques from computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions state spaces and probabilistic completeness, which are concepts from control systems (cs.SY) and machine learning (cs.LG), respectively.
